headline: Jézabel Couppey-Soubeyran: 'What if the stock market euphoria over AI is just a bubble within the larger financial bubble?'
description: In her column, the economist points out that the financial markets have been inflated by decades of monetary policy tailored to their needs. She warns that it is the collapse of this broader bubble, not just that of artificial intelligence, which should be of greatest concern.

headline: Croatia qualify for 2026 World Cup as Netherlands edge closer and Germany stall
description: Croatia sealed their place at the 2026 World Cup with a shaky 3–1 win over the Faroe Islands on a night when the Netherlands all but secured qualification and Germany were pushed to the brink by Luxembourg.

headline: By handing over writing to AI, we risk preventing ourselves from thinking
description: Writing is not just a means of communication; it helps us organize our thoughts. Turning to artificial intelligence text generators ultimately means allowing Silicon Valley billionaires to think in our place.

headline: 'Delhi is no longer livable': Deadly pollution in Indian capital claims more than 17,000 lives each year
description: Millions of firecrackers set off during the Hindu festival of Diwali at the end of October have worsened the already extreme fine particle pollution engulfing the megacity. Every winter, Delhi's 30 million residents face a toxic nightmare, while blistering heat waves strike the city each summer.

headline: Le Creuset turns 100: 'We are lucky to have a fanbase that loves to show off their Dutch ovens'
